From 7c160a5d1748b30971a444c61a4ef0599980f613 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 14:25:51 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] fix(concierge): preserve V2 memory across every history
 writer
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fixes a runtime-integration defect: pushAssistant (used by background inspection notifications) called
loadHistory → saveHistory, which parsed the stored JSON as a bare Message[] and wrote a bare array —
silently CLOBBERING the V2 envelope's activeTask. A proactive "your plan is ready" DM during an active
run erased the run state.

  - mergeMemory() (task-run.ts) is the single, pure WRITE codec: given the current stored raw + new
    messages, it PRESERVES the existing activeTask + summary + recentTools unless explicitly overridden
    (opts.activeTask === null clears it). It emits a V2 envelope when a task exists, else a legacy bare
    array (byte-identical to pre-V2 storage). readMemory is the matching read codec (both formats).
  - concierge.ts now routes EVERY writer through one persistHistory() = saveChatMessages(mergeMemory(...)):
    saveHistory, pushAssistant (background notices), and the turn-end shadow persist. A background write
    can no longer drop an active run, and two interleaved writers can lose at most a message, never the
    authoritative task state (each re-reads + preserves the task).

Tests: mergeMemory preserves the activeTask when a background writer only appends messages; writes a
legacy array when there is no run (byte-identical off-mode); and can explicitly clear the task. Off mode
stays behaviorally identical; the full telegram suite (78) is green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
