From 519c66f2886164b017eb782bb0afc961460a0b33 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 14:31:50 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] fix(concierge): make lifecycle tool outcomes strict and
 authoritative
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the permissive `data.ok !== false && !data.error` parsing in mapConciergeTool with STRICT
per-tool decoders, so a payout-critical tool can never reach "success" on a guess.

  - sage_fund_and_launch fails closed: a missing campaignId, empty output, prose, malformed JSON,
    error payload, or timeout becomes AMBIGUOUS (ok:false + ambiguousTimeout → the controller runs the
    read-only verify flow before any second spend) — NEVER a transition to active. An id is never
    inferred from prose. Explicit business stops map to hard reasons (needsFunding/needsGas/overCap).
  - lifecycleOutcome() labels each decoded result success|failed|ambiguous|needs_funding|needs_gas|
    over_cap; ShadowStep now records that real outcome, and recentTools no longer serialize every call
    as ok:true.
  - Loop detection: the same tool firing >=3x with no state progress blocks the run (steps flagged
    loop). The unused lastCallSig state/claim on TaskRunV1 is removed.
  - Surface-aware: on web (no money tools) a fund_and_launch result is never observed as a lifecycle
    event — web-chat telemetry can't pretend to authorize Telegram-only funding.
  - Approval is bound to the plan the run is awaiting: a "yes" that references a changed/stale plan id
    is not honored (re-present instead of deploying a different plan).

Tests: a fund result with no id (6 malformed/empty/prose variants) never reaches active; strict decoder
+ outcome labels; web skips money; loop→blocked; ShadowStep records the real outcome; stale approval not
honored. Full telegram suite green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
