From d492ca415511f0f3ff712319d7eac780081713cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 14:45:16 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] fix(agentic): make inspection replay positively safe and
 faithful
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A transition was marked safeClassification="safe" even when its network behavior was "not_captured", so
an unverified action could be replayed. Now safety must be POSITIVELY established.

  - The field test's request interceptor records the HTTP methods per transition (a shared buffer drained
    by capture() into FieldTestState.networkMethods — additive, digest-neutral). deriveObservations maps
    them: GET/HEAD-only → get_observed → `safe`; a mutating method → state_changing; nothing recorded →
    `not_captured` → `unverified`. buildProbe replays ONLY `safe` transitions, so an unverified or
    state-changing transition is refused (fail-safe when no network was captured).
  - The replay locator is built from the BEFORE-state target element (the control that was acted on), not
    the after-state notable elements (which are the RESULT of the action).
  - Key actions use an explicit ALLOWLIST (allowedKey): Space/Enter/Escape/Tab/Arrows/single char. An
    unknown key returns null and the probe is rejected — there is NO Enter fallback that would synthesize
    an action Sage never observed. buildProbe rejects a press whose key isn't allowlisted.

Tests: an unverified transition is rejected; a press with an off-allowlist key is rejected; allowedKey
is a strict allowlist (unknown → null). The real-browser replay suite (7) stays green; fixtures across
the observation/mission/demo suites carry networkMethods so their transitions are positively safe.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
