From ea2415549481f31d6cd45b08b42b15faa678f98f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 15:12:47 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] fix(concierge): atomic history append + full
 approval-token binding
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the two P0 gaps the review flagged.

  - CONCURRENCY: the turn-end write and pushAssistant now go through an ATOMIC appendHistory() that
    re-reads the current stored history and appends only the new messages. Because better-sqlite3
    load+save here is synchronous with no await between them, a concurrent user turn and background
    notification cannot interleave — each append lands whole, so neither a message NOR the activeTask is
    lost (the prior code overwrote with a start-of-turn snapshot, dropping a mid-turn background message).
  - APPROVAL BINDING: a "yes" is now bound to the EXACT plan token — plan id + plan digest + budget text +
    approval revision (approvalToken). Entering awaiting_approval stamps the token and bumps the revision;
    observeFounder honors the approval only when the run STILL matches that token, so a re-inspection that
    changes the plan or budget invalidates a stale approval. The get_inspection decoder now threads
    planDigest through.

Tests: the stale-approval case (plan digest changed out from under the founder → "yes" not honored;
restored → honored); mergeMemory preserve-both still green. Full telegram suite (84) passes; off mode
byte-identical.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
